The Durban University of Technology. DURBAN - The Durban University of Technology is closing four of its campuses temporarily. This follows violent student protests on Thursday. READ: DUT says protests have caused serious damage to campuses Studies are set to continue online. The university's spokesperson, Alan Khan, says property has been damaged in the attack. READ: DUT protests | University temporarily suspends operations DUT will not hesitate to evacuate its residences. Last month, protests led to the closure of three of its campuses.